  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nThe `node`, `npm`, and `nvm` commands have a `--version` flag, but the truffle equivalent is `truffle version`.\r\nIf the user runs `truffle --version`, the output is unexpected. \r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nGiven truffle  v5.5.13 and\r\nnode 14:\r\n```\r\n> truffle --version\r\n1.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nnode 16:\r\n```\r\n> truffle --version\r\nunknown\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`truffle --version` should be an alias of `truffle version` and return the expected output. Something like:\r\n```\r\nTruffle v5.5.13 (core: 5.5.13)\r\nGanache v^7.1.0\r\nSolidity v0.5.16 (solc-js)\r\nNode v16.9.1\r\nWeb3.js v1.5.3\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe user hurts itself in confusion! \r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS 12.3.1\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`):  v5.5.13\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 14 or 16\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  8.10.0\r\n",
